The paper deals with stochastic matching, which is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT). The authors use techniques from probability theory and analysis of algorithms, which are also relevant to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses information theory and communication complexity, which fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
